data.text:
Slint

Slint was an American rock band formed in 1986 in Louisville, Kentucky. The band’s unique sound blended elements of post-rock, math rock, post-hardcore, and indie rock.

Post-rock Dream pop Math rock Slowcore Shoegaze Alternative rock Experimental rock Louisville underground Noise pop Post-hardcore Post-punk
